saster?…If your deepest self is singing and coaxing you straight toward the bonfire, is it better to turn away? Stop your ears with wax? Ignore all the perverse glory your heart is screaming at you? Set yourself on the course that will lead you dutifully towards the norm, reasonable hours and regular medical check-ups, stable relationships and steady career advancement the New York Times and brunch on Sunday, all with the promise of being somehow a better person? Or…is it better to throw yourself head first and laughing into the holy rage calling your name?', 1269, 0), (136782, 'Begin to pursue your dream.', 2878, 0), (136783, 'A man is always right to pursue the thing he loves.No matter even if it kills him?I think so. Yes. No matter what.', 548, 0), (136784, 'Writing is a holy occupation.', 2878, 0), (136785, 'I''m more depressed about the realities of the mature bureaucracy and more excited about the ideal that we''re fighting for. And the juxtaposition has obvious consequences. Rolf Mowatt-Larrsen', 19672, 0), (136786, 'I am a woman who’s passionate about life. Perhaps too full of passion for the majority of the world to understand. I lust for adventure and stories; I feel everything. I’m a lover and a fighter. I fight for what I love and I love what I fight for. I yearn for what is more than life, and I live beyond that yearning.', 25990, 0), (136787, 'When you are clear on your calling, you command the universe to submit to your voice', 5532, 0), (136788, 'I have hunger for your mouth, for your voice, for your hair', 12, 0), (136789, 'I touched you and my life stopped', 12, 0), (136790, 'Oh invade me with your scalding mouth,search me if you like, with your nocturnal eyes,but allow me to sail and sleep upon your name.', 12, 0), (136791, 'Love, my territory of kisses and volcanoes.', 12, 0), (136792, 'I love the piece of earth you are,because in all the planetary prairiesI do not have another star. You repeatthe multiplication of the universe.', 12, 0), (136793, 'beyond the earth and the shadowthe brightness of our love will stay alive', 12, 0), (136794, 'I repeated: come with me, as if I were dying,and no one saw in my mouth the moon that was bleeding,no one saw the blood that was rising into the silence.Oh love, now let us forget the star with thorns!', 12, 0), (136795, 'Of so much moon were your hips to me,of all the sun your deep mouth and its delight,of so much burning light like honey in the shade', 12, 0), (136796, 'Make Your wish Your Dream and Your Dream Your Goal', 25991, 0), (136797, 'A vigorous temper is not altogether an evil. Men who are as easy as an old shoe are generally of as lttle worth .', 771, 0), (136798, 'I paint the darkness and the silence, You see them as stars and poetry.', 8495, 0), (136799, 'Find your passion, it makes all the difference.', 11121, 0), (136800, 'Heart language is logic set on fire.', 771, 0);
