INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (136901, 'I take small, shallow breaths, even though my lungs are begging for more air. I feel the heat of Ten’s controlled breaths against my face. As we stand there, it feels as if an electric charge is growing between us, so powerful that it would shock us if we moved even a millimeter closer together. And yet I feel like I want to.', 25999, 0), (136902, 'They clutch and cling and howl when I leave them, but how badly they love.', 23, 0), (136903, 'Where the world saw ''nothing''', 26000, 0), (136904, 'There is no greater success than turning your true passion into a dream, and seeing its reality come to manifestation.', 166, 0), (136905, 'Don’t whittle your potential, just because others don’t believe in you. The only worthy question is “Do You Believe in You?', 18974, 0), (136906, 'Find your mission and live it with all your might.', 2878, 0), (136907, 'Rise and shine! The Lord’s anointing is upon you.', 2878, 0), (136908, '[Speaking about writing her first novel] You have to be passionate enough about it and I was.', 23883, 0), (136909, 'Identify your divine gift and use it to serve humanity.', 2878, 0), (136910, 'Without empathy and love there is no morality, no altruism, no compassion for others. The scientific mindset, like the artistic and spiritual ones, must be passionate and not easily dissuaded from its path. Although, the empirical mindset must be ever more vigilant than the artist because there is much more at stake than just individual freedom, there is the very basis for truthful inquiry.', 3550, 0), (136911, 'Find your passion and live your best life.', 2878, 0), (136912, 'Make the most of your sacred life on earth.', 2878, 0), (136913, 'Early morning exercise will keep you active for the entire day.', 2878, 0), (136914, 'There''s no such thing as having something to fall back on in life, there''s passion, talent, skills, compassion and purpose. Choice is a prerequisite', 22197, 0), (136915, 'I love the sacred moment.', 2878, 0), (136916, 'Plans become Platitudes, if you don''t have Passion and Persistence to Execute them!', 18974, 0), (136917, 'With great passion, observe every details of the sacred journey.', 2878, 0), (136918, 'Work with great zeal.', 2878, 0), (136919, 'Passions cannot take wings in adversity, and adversities remain prevalent because of dormant passions.', 14742, 0), (136920, 'And worse, far worse – he wasn''t just kissing me. He was making me like it! And he was somehow, by some nefarious chauvinistic manly trick managing to make me kiss him back!', 2483, 0), (136921, 'His lips reached mine and enveloped them, soft as velvet and yet unyielding.', 2483, 0), (136922, 'His silent, stony face was only inches away now. He was so near, so terribly near – and then he moved to close the last bit of distance.', 2483, 0), (136923, 'Before she could stop her hands, they reached for him, as though they existed for no other reason than to touch him. Her fingers brushed across his jaw with a feather''s caress before pulling away, and he closed his eyes on a soft inhale. Like the poison toying with its remedy, Shahrzad''s hands ignored her and took control, a mere taste of his skin not nearly enough. Never enough.', 333, 0), (136924, 'Love and peace are not just words, they are a way of life. And in an honest living, love will always conquer.', 15173, 0), (136925, 'Reason, ruling alone, is a force confining; and passion, unattended, is a flame that burns to its own destruction.', 81, 0), (136926, 'She was drowning in sandalwood and sunlight. Time ceased to be more than a notion. Her lips were hers one moment. And then they were his. The taste of him on her tongue was like sun-warmed honey. Like cool water sliding down her parched throat. Like the promise of all her tomorrows in a single sigh. When she wound her fingers in his hair to draw her body against his, he stilled for breath, and she knew, as he knew, that they were lost. Lost forever. In this kiss. This kiss that would change everything.', 333, 0), (136927, 'I will pursue the dream, no matter how long it takes to fulfil it.', 2878, 0), (136928, 'We do not have to go in search of passion. Instead we need to search for God, who plants the seed of passion in our hearts.', 26001, 0), (136929, 'Passion is not what gives you bliss or makes you happy 24/7, but what you''re willing to suffer for, what you genuinely believe to be worth the sacrifice.', 26002, 0), (136930, 'The universe is a life giving force that is part of us. It flows in harmony through us guiding our every step. It maintain the harmony and flow of life. It gives us the passion and the knowledge we need to live and be inspired by. Yet in return, it is inspired by the human spirit', 3821, 0), (136931, 'Education, possessions, or people cannot replace passion, but they are given meaning by your passion in life.', 15050, 0), (136932, 'Passion is the mother of every greatness.', 166, 0), (136933, 'Let your passion serve as your energy source to keep you going. I can attest that you will be happier, healthier, and more successful at it.', 26003, 0), (136934, 'When your emotion finds a true expression in other person, he''s your soul mate. Never leave him!', 12721, 0), (136935, 'I write to express and I shop to destress', 5149, 0), (136936, 'Be informed here and now that incessant prayers does  not finger God to open the Windows of heaven. What God wants to see Is your passion towards success and your giving drive...nothing else!', 332, 0), (136937, 'The time is now. What you have to do, do it now.', 2878, 0), (136938, 'Let your passion serve as your energy source to keep you going.', 26003, 0), (136939, 'Be daring, be passionate and persistently pursue your dreams.', 2878, 0), (136940, 'There’s a pressure at all hours of the day only a poem can assuage.', 11690, 0), (136941, 'The impulse to touch her and all the life in her was something I had to check regularly.', 22465, 0), (136942, 'When you look back with regret, that (regret, loss) becomes your focus. Then your focus directs you: you go back to that – again and again.Choose a new rudder: Look forward now – and focus on your passion with joyful anticipation.Then your passion will fill the empty space of your loss...and where you land up will amaze you!', 26004, 0), (136943, 'When you look back with regret, that (regret, loss) becomes your focus. Then your focus directs you: you go back to that – again and again.Look forward now – and focus on your passions with joyful anticipation.Then your passion will fill the gap of your loss...and where you land us will amaze you!', 26004, 0), (136944, 'I hope to inspire you to recognize that your reason for existence is to pursue the things that excite you the most. The best thing you can do--for yourself and everyone else--is to act on the things you''re most passionate about. When you do, you''ll shine, and everyone else will see that brilliance.On a biological level, the mirror neutrons of the people around you will activate. They will recognize that they can also follow their dreams and accomplish things they have always wanted to accomplish. On a spiritual level, their souls will remember their reason for being.', 26005, 0), (136945, 'I believe eros dwells in our innermost being as the spirit of creative expression. To me, eros is a great path that we must walk, a song we listen to, a game that we hunt and enjoy, a lesson to learn, a garden where flowers bloom, a prodigious puzzle to solve, a book to read, a chapter to write, and an ocean to swim in. That’s what eros is to me.', 19461, 0), (136946, 'Suicide is a confession of failure. And like divorce, it is shrouded in excuses and rationalizations spun endlessly to disguise the simple fact that all one''s energy, passion, appetite and ambition have been aborted.', 8153, 0), (136947, 'Men hate passion, any great passion. Henry Cameron made a mistake : he loved his work. That was why he fought. That was why he lost.', 631, 0), (136948, 'and this passion, like bad kerosene, barely burns.', 26006, 0), (136949, 'What is the point of all the money in the world if you don''t have the freedom to do the things you love?', 5149, 0), (136950, 'What I Have Lived ForThree passions, simple but overwhelmingly strong, have governed my life: the longing for love, the search for knowledge, and unbearable pity for the suffering of mankind. These passions, like great winds, have blown me hither and thither, in a wayward course, over a great ocean of anguish, reaching to the very verge of despair. I have sought love, first, because it brings ecstasy - ecstasy so great that I would often have sacrificed all the rest of life for a few hours of this joy. I have sought it, next, because it relieves loneliness--that terrible loneliness in which one shivering consciousness looks over the rim of the world into the cold unfathomable lifeless abyss. I have sought it finally, because in the union of love I have seen, in a mystic miniature, the prefiguring vision of the heaven that saints and poets have imagined. This is what I sought, and though it might seem too good for human life, this is what--at last--I have found.With equal passion I have sought knowledge. I have wished to understand the hearts of men. I have wished to know why the stars shine. And I have tried to apprehend the Pythagorean power by which number holds sway above the flux. A little of this, but not much, I have achieved. Love and knowledge, so far as they were possible, led upward toward the heavens. But always pity brought me back to earth. Echoes of cries of pain reverberate in my heart. Children in famine, victims tortured by oppressors, helpless old people a burden to their sons, and the whole world of loneliness, poverty, and pain make a mockery of what human life should be. I long to alleviate this evil, but I cannot, and I too suffer. This has been my life. I have found it worth living, and would gladly live it again if the chance were offered me.', 95, 0);
