wrong, smelled wrong and tasted wrong. I thought I would get over it. I hoped it would go away. I wanted to be free of Hanna. But I never got over the feeling that something was wrong.', 628, 0), (137214, 'Begin your new year by making a commitment to yourself. Rediscover your passion. What sets your heart on fire? And do something about it. Take action. Today. Now.', 24141, 0), (137215, 'Do not get lost in the flow of reality.', 11253, 0), (137216, 'Don''t exploit your enemy''s weakness, for he may have none.Exploit his passions and the battle is yours.', 26044, 0), (137217, 'As they made their way to the coast, he bemoaned the hotel trade in the manner, Dorrigo felt, that those who love what they do bemoan their passion the most.', 9692, 0), (137218, 'I want to get lose in your eyes and be brought back to reality with your kisses.', 7384, 0), (137219, 'Big Love and More Light!XxMwaaahhhhXx', 26045, 0), (137220, 'Dear God, Lisa, give me back my peace of mind!', 26041, 0), (137221, 'Forbid statements like “will God ever meet me?”, “am I worthy of his blessings?”, “I am not sure God will bless me”, “what shows that I am blessed?”. These statements clearly tell that you are not aware of who you are in the first place.', 3301, 0), (137222, 'Grow taller than your failures', 26046, 0), (137223, 'We await their creative interpretations of works by others and we love how they freely adapt and alter the music we like and enjoy. The wonderful magical alchemy they co-create is enough to spur the imagination of the audience. There is no need for other instruments or vocals. The music alone suffices. Listening to them, we can close our eyes and be taken away to a faraway place, we can envision a story or embellish a memory. We can connect to spirit and source and what we connect to in our deepest being is akin to religious experience. They dedicate themselves to each performance fearlessly, courageously, passionately, and generously.', 26047, 0), (137224, 'Follow your passion? 