ed her tears with mine. ~ Erik', 830, 0), (137236, 'When the vision fills your brain and passion hits your gut, the need to write it down cannot be stifled. (Marti Melville)', 6819, 0), (137237, 'Never wait for the alarm clock to wake you up', 26048, 0), (137238, 'When this reality, the one and only power that checks and disciplines man from within, vanishes because belief in it is slackening, the social domain falls prey to passions. The ensuing vacuum is filled by the gas of emotion. Everyone proclaims what best suits his interests, his whims, his intellectual manias. To escape the void and the perplexities of his own soul, a man will rush to join any party standard that is being carried through the streets. With society gone there remain only parties.', 2800, 0), (137239, 'Progress across the time axis is passive. Progress up the results axis is passion.', 10209, 0), (137240, 'Your little kettle will rattle in the battle', 26049, 0), (137241, 'Men seek a great deal, but fatally close, albeit very different, is one''s pride in proving oneself right with one''s zeal for finding the truth.', 230, 0), (137242, 'What do you always think about? What do you think you can do easily? What do you find peace in your heart to do? Watch those things carefully because among them is something on which you can turn the entire environment surrounding you for your success.', 3301, 0), (137243, 'When the vision fill yours mind and passio hits your gut, the need to write it down cannot be stifled.', 6819, 0), (137244, 'Dreaming is the art of thinking deep about who you want to be, what you are moved by your God-guided passion to do and what you are convinced to be the passion that moves the machinery of your body', 3301, 0), (137245, 'And from the look on his face I could see he was one of the lucky ones, one of those people who like doing what they''re good at. That''s rare. When you see that in a person, you can''t miss it.', 1594, 0), (137246, 'It’s our(As The Stars of the Sky Foundation, Inc.) passion and joy to read to children and improve literacy, as well as teach others about charity and the impact they can have in a child’s life.', 24623, 0), (137247, 'Ordinary people can do extra ordinary things when they create opportunity towards their passion', 12584, 0), (137248, '[A]though people get paid to do their jobs, you cannot pay someone to do their job passionately and wholeheartedly. Those qualities are not for sale; they are themselves gifts that can only be given freely, and are in many, many fields.', 797, 0), (137249, 'If writing is your passion, write and don’t let anyone else convince you otherwise. You don’t need to quit your day job to do it. Create a realistic schedule and stick with it.', 26050, 0), (137250, 'To lust for something is desire turned selfish and gone mad. To embrace God’s passion is desire turned selfless and gone mindful.', 4397, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (137251, 'It wasn’t often he met someone who had her emotions so on display. Most of the women he knew were interested in more material things and kept their emotions well hidden beneath a mask of sophistication. It was refreshing to find someone who was so natural – so passionate.', 26051, 0), (137252, 'Embrace love', 26052, 0), (137253, 'Rosa had achieved the sort of serene and confident happiness that Tamsin had never really known. She was connected to Roberto in a way that made Tamsin long for something similar. A man with whom she could share all parts of her life, someone to be her equal and her inspiration.', 26051, 0), (137254, 'God’s grace does not require a condition to abound. However to obtain the promises of his blessings, you have to strive for it, fight for it, work hard for it and insist upon it.', 3301, 0), (137255, 'You break me the hardest, make me the strongest, and keep me the softest.', 330, 0), (137256, 'Live for a reasonLive with passion.', 2586, 0), (137257, 'The death of a dream is the day that you stop believing in the work it takes to get there.', 4193, 0), (137258, 'Happiness is not in wealth or splendor, but in passion, perception, and pursuit.', 2586, 0), (137259, 'I want love, passion, honesty, and companionship... sex that drives me crazy and conversation that drives me sane.', 161, 0), (137260, 'Do your own thing with love and passion. You will be happy, no matter the result of your action.', 2586, 0), (137261, 'Passion for compassion will give you happiness.', 2586, 0), (137262, 'Never raise your voice but raise yourself and your passion for love and life.', 2586, 0), (137263, 'We live in wonder, blaze in a cycle of passion and apprehension.', 8078, 0), (137264, 'Your passions don’t have to connect to one another and no one needs to sign off on them. Passion isn’t logical… it’s only the fuel which keeps our souls alive. Let it be that simple.', 1534, 0), (137265, 'Love is one of the most motivating and self-defining forces in our lives, whether we turn from it or allow ourselves to be drawn to it. If you allow romantic possibilities with others to consume all your time and energy, they will distract you from the things of interest that fill your life with passion and purpose.', 3424, 0), (137266, 'The heart pointed to the brain and said with great disdain, “Those who live their lives in here live the lives most full of fear.', 10209, 0), (137267, 'Face each day with radiant, nurturing love, confidence, a bright vision and creativity with enduring determination and strength matched with a breathing courage as you happily embrace your responsibility and growth in many areas of life. Combine your energy and joy, your passion and vision in creating a brighter day.', 15605, 0), (137268, 'Gratitude is uplifting and helps you glow, stay beautiful, and feel eternally young as it churns up zeal and undying enthusiasm.', 26053, 0), (137269, 'To become a distinguished entrepreneur, you need to have an undeniable, unquestionable and unmovable passion for your vision.', 24838, 0), (137270, 'All the answers i seek lie within me, but inner quietude is mandatory before those become loud and clear.', 26053, 0), (137271, 'The light that colors the embraces the gods is the light that resides in your heart.', 26053, 0), (137272, 'We have to believe that our prayers, if pure and powerful can transform any catastrophic situation, regardless of its magnitude.', 26053, 0), (137273, 'Obstacles accelerate transformation', 26053, 0), (137274, 'Every answer I seek lies within me. Any outward seeking for my answers can only take me as far as my inner self permits.', 26053, 0), (137275, 'Let your light shine.', 26053, 0), (137276, 'How true is the observation that unrequited love turns to deepest hate.', 24527, 0), (137277, 'The days seem short, and time seems too little to do what you love.', 15050, 0), (137278, 'Not Every Battle You Lose is considered as a loss sometimes this loss leads to the best victory, You just have to be Patient and to take advantage Of every unexpected event that happened during your struggle your own war .', 26054, 0), (137279, 'Those with calling also find wealth, so jump and start swimming towards your true self.', 10209, 0), (137280, 'Awakening others is an impossible endeavor until I myself am awakened.', 26053, 0), (137281, 'Through powerful and heartfelt communication with the universe, you can create a new world everyday-you can be proud of.', 26053, 0), (137282, 'Life is about finding yourself. Finding yourself is about finding your ultimate goal, ultimate passion.', 2586, 0), (137283, 'I always thought that falling in love should feel like jumping from a cliff. A fall that scares you as much as it excites you, that leaves you breathless and wanting more. The impossible kind … that ruins you for everyone else. This wasn’t it, and my chances of finding it have just become harder. I am not the same girl that I was before. Finding that special guy prepared to carry my load with me, would be one in a million, a fairytale come true, and just maybe, an impossible dream…', 26055, 0), (137284, 'Knowing God is like listening to beautiful music. His words have power. He lifts me up & soothes my soul. He makes me dance. He gives me joy.', 2736, 0), (137285, 'I love doing it. Every building is like a person. Single and unrepeatable.', 631, 0), (137286, 'Mind can be your best friend or worst enemy.', 26056, 0), (137287, 'Commitment is the foundation of focus.', 290, 0), (137288, 'No matter how they fought they had always been like this: balanced between anger and passion, between hurt and glory. When they first got together, she didn''t understand how two people who had so little in common could be so madly, passionately in love. When they split, she had realized madness and passion could never keep a couple together.', 4925, 0), (137289, 'Real life starts when you are doing something you love out of passion.', 9273, 0), (137290, 'Beginning is scary, exciting, terrifying, and all things amazing. Begin even when you''re not sure.....What do you have to lose?', 4193, 0), (137291, 'My breath caught fire and my heart leapt infinite beats within his proximity."Wreck me, tame me. The way you want it." I whispered my plea.His foggy grey eyes glinted with desire and lust. "I will". The two words were my end as well as the beginning of something new and insurmountable between us.', 26057, 0), (137292, 'Loving someone is sticking a pin through a voodoo doll and not hitting any vital organs', 11975, 0), (137293, 'Couldn''t I for once have you and the work at the same time?', 555, 0), (137294, 'Let your feelings flow and the scribbled words stay as a sovereign of the moment.', 7700, 0), (137295, 'As a Priest got a calling to preach, you also got a calling to do whatever you do, so do it with passion and only God can stop your calling.', 9273, 0), (137296, 'Grab tightly to the reigns of passion and ride into glory for without it life would be stagnant and you would be a spirit without cause.', 3711, 0), (137297, 'But without going to such extremes prudence may easily involve the loss of some of the best things in life. The worshipper of Dionysus reacts against prudence. In intoxication, physical or spiritual, he recovers an intensity of feeling which prudence had destroyed; he finds the world full of delight and beauty, and his imagination is suddenly liberated from the prison of every-day preoccupations.', 95, 0), (137298, 'In the modern Christian attempt to take a stand as Christ did, and maybe for others, win the approval of the world, the Christian will often think that it consists of targeting and demoralizing fellow Christians and only fellow Christians. It is one thing to stand against religious hypocrisy when one sees it, but it is another to go on snorting at anything or anyone who might seem ''too Christian'' to us. The irony is that by doing this we are further advoc